The White House is preparing for the 2020 Christmas season and inviting volunteers to help decorate. Interested individuals can apply to decorate the White House and serve as greeters at the Holiday Open Houses. Musicians, including bands, choirs, and Christmas-themed entertainers, can also apply to perform during the events. Due to COVID-19, there will be new policies in place to ensure a safe environment, including social distancing, wearing face coverings, and using hand sanitizer stations. The application deadline for volunteers is October 1st, and for musicians is October 8th. Applicants will be notified of their acceptance by October 15th and October 22nd respectively. Any inquiries can be directed to Volunteers@who.eop.gov.